or Thomas Neville , sometimes called Thomas the Bastard , or the Bastard of Fauconberg ( 1429 – 22 September 1471 ) , was the natural son of William Neville , Lord Fauconberg , who was a leading commander in the Hundred Years ' War and , until joining his cousin , Richard Neville ( “ Warwick the Kingmaker “ ) in rebellion against another cousin , Edward IV , served on the Yorkist side in the Wars of the Roses .
